messages.message:
General Info:
To run AIHub locally, you need to setup a few config values. Putting these into env-local.json is annoying as it might conflict with git pull and show up in git status.
Instead put it into `env-local-overrides.json`
This file sits at `shared-utils/build-utils/shared/env-local-overrides.json` right next to `env-local.json`. It is is git ignored, so will not be checked in. As the name suggests, values set in this override the values in `env-local.json`
```{
  "base": {

  },
  "local": {
  	"aws_access_key_id": "XX",
	  "aws_secret_access_key": "XX"
  },
  "aihub-local": {

  },
  "docker-local": {
    "openai_api_key": "XX"
  }
}```

To add more color, we don't have to add the values based on "base", "local", "aihub-local". Since
`env-local-overrides.json` overrides `env-local.json`, we can put it in "base" directly (more detail (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/55158)).

For example, I have these and I'll copy over config in "st-aihub" or "st-aihub-saml" to "base" depending on whichever scenario I'm developing in
```{
  "base": {

  },
  "st-aihub": {

  },
  "st-aihub-saml": {

  }
}```
